I wanted to provide an update and seek feedback on next steps for engaging with
American Stock Transfer.
American Stock Transfer has confirmed they do not have bandwidth to take on any
new transfer agent clients for the remainder of 2018. For comparison, we also
reached to VStock, and they have also confirmed that they will not be onboarding new
clients until 2019 (see attached).
As a reminder, it is my understanding that we are currently in "breach" of the warrants
due to the following provision:
Section 4. Stock Certificates.
If the Company shall at any time change to a stock
certificate format, the Company shall at all times have
authorized, unissued and otherwise unreserved, a
sufficient number of shares of Common Stock to
enable it to satisfy any and all Conversion Shares
pursuant to the terms of the Warrant. The Company
agrees to maintain a transfer agent for its Common
Stock so long as the Warrants are outstanding.

The first is in the definition of Conversion Shares, and there is no definition for
"Conversion Shares" in the warrant. Regardless, since we do not have a certificate
format for our stock (nor do we plan to issue one), this provision is technically not
applicable.
The second comes from the statement to "maintain a transfer agent for its Common
Stock so long as the Warrants are outstanding." Given we do not have Stock
Certificates in the truest sense, we would need some degree of transfer agent
relationship to issue Conversion Shares as the warrants convert. Since we do not
have a transfer agent, we are not in compliance with this provision.
We can consider a couple options:
Issue a Board Resolution stating that, as CFO, will take on all responsibilities
in the interim. This is not the cleanest solution, and I would not present it to
CardConnect as our solution.
